comment.narrative:
Ethnic minorities possess a rich and distinctive way of life set against a unique natural, social, cultural and historical backdrop. If properly preserved, managed and developed, these rich cultural and natural resources can be used as a strong driver for local socio-economic development. However, a number of obstacles hinder ethnic minority women seeking to make a start in business:
- Low confidence due to perceived low social status and low educational status;
- A lack of education on how to establish and run a business;
- A lack of financial support; and
- Cultural traditions that make a male breadwinner/ female caregiver model the expected norm.

